moa_t3db: Inorganic and organic tin compounds are weak inhibitors of alcohol dehydrogenase. (A183); Organotins are endocrine disruptors and are believed to contribute to obesity by inappropriate activation of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor gamma, leading to adipocyte differentiation. (A184); Organotins inhibit the chymotrypsin-like activity of 20S and cellular proteasomes by binding to the beta-5 subunit. This results in apoptosis caused by downstream effects in the proteasome pathway. (A181); Organotins are endocrine disruptors and are believed to contribute to obesity by inappropriate activation of retinoic acid receptors, leading to adipocyte differentiation. (A184)
